    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Lancaster was formed in 1651 from Northumberland and York counties.  
</p>
      <p>The will books of Lancaster County in this collection were created by the County Court.
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Will Books, 1674-1795, of Lancaster County Court. The will book includes the name of testator, list of heirs and year the wills were proven in court and probate records such as inventories and appraisements.  All of the volumes have indexes except, 1690-1709 and 1770-1783.
</p>
    </scopecontent>
